1
00:00:14,167 --> 00:00:15,633
<i> What are you doing?</i>

2
00:00:15,767 --> 00:00:17,067
<i> Let's go!</i>

3
00:00:20,367 --> 00:00:21,300
<i> Where are you?</i>

4
00:00:21,433 --> 00:00:22,700
<i> Emma!</i>

5
00:00:22,833 --> 00:00:24,000
<i> She's gone!</i>

6
00:00:24,133 --> 00:00:25,767
<i> She escaped you again!</i>

7
00:00:25,900 --> 00:00:27,233
<i> No!</i>

8
00:00:27,367 --> 00:00:30,167
<i> I consulted a doctor.</i>

9
00:00:30,300 --> 00:00:31,900
<i>I was told I have
a mental condition.</i>

10
00:00:32,033 --> 00:00:35,433
<i>So, you're the reason my
daughter became a monster.</i>

11
00:00:35,600 --> 00:00:37,433
<i> And you didn't tell me!</i>

12
00:00:37,567 --> 00:00:40,167
<i> Once she takes the Pryvaxil,</i>

13
00:00:40,300 --> 00:00:41,567
<i> she'll return to her senses.</i>

14
00:00:41,700 --> 00:00:43,267
<i> Then, let's fight her head-on.</i>

15
00:00:43,400 --> 00:00:45,767
<i>I will no longer hide in Olive's
insanity.</i>

16
00:00:45,900 --> 00:00:47,733
<i>Jade, someone has tampered
with your medicine.</i>

17
00:00:47,867 --> 00:00:48,733
<i> It was Flor.</i>

18
00:00:48,867 --> 00:00:50,167
<i> You don't love me enough.</i>

19
00:00:50,300 --> 00:00:52,900
<i>But fine. I'll do what you want.</i>

20
00:00:53,033 --> 00:00:54,100
<i> I'll choose Mom.</i>

21
00:00:54,233 --> 00:00:56,633
<i>But don't expect that we will
still be friends.</i>

22
00:01:42,833 --> 00:01:43,633
Baby girl?

23
00:01:44,667 --> 00:01:45,767
Baby girl.

24
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:49,300
Thank you so much.

25
00:01:50,333 --> 00:01:52,233
Thank you for forgiving me.

26
00:01:52,367 --> 00:01:55,000
Aunt Jade, you deserve it.

27
00:01:55,133 --> 00:01:58,167
I saw how you handled
your problems.

28
00:01:58,300 --> 00:02:01,500
And you sought professional
help.

29
00:02:02,533 --> 00:02:06,567
By the way,
how are you and Zayn?

30
00:02:06,700 --> 00:02:09,567
I saw his posts on social media.

31
00:02:09,700 --> 00:02:14,000
He seems to be lonely
and not doing well.

32
00:02:14,167 --> 00:02:18,100
I blocked Zayn from my
social media accounts.

33
00:02:18,233 --> 00:02:21,800
I get hurt whenever I see him.

34
00:02:21,933 --> 00:02:24,833
It's gonna be okay.

35
00:02:24,967 --> 00:02:28,267
Jade, have you already taken
your medicines?

36
00:02:30,067 --> 00:02:32,000
Yes, love. I took them.

37
00:02:32,133 --> 00:02:35,833
And I do everything
the doctor told me

38
00:02:35,967 --> 00:02:37,267
to avoid getting stressed.

39
00:02:37,400 --> 00:02:38,733
From now on,

40
00:02:38,867 --> 00:02:41,933
I will no longer worry about
the Artemis Pharmacy.

41
00:02:42,067 --> 00:02:43,533
Astrid is back anyway.

42
00:02:43,667 --> 00:02:46,433
And she will handle the
problem with Activora.

43
00:02:48,700 --> 00:02:49,733
Love...

44
00:02:51,233 --> 00:02:52,300
baby girl...

45
00:02:53,467 --> 00:02:56,233
thank you so much.

46
00:02:56,367 --> 00:03:01,967
You never left me when I wasn't
in my right mind.

47
00:03:03,100 --> 00:03:05,367
You were always there to support
me.

48
00:03:05,500 --> 00:03:07,567
You've been there for me.

49
00:03:07,700 --> 00:03:10,433
I'm so lucky to have you both
as my family.

50
00:03:12,100 --> 00:03:16,600
We will always have each other's
back.

51
00:03:16,733 --> 00:03:19,067
If Mom is here...

52
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:20,933
you're Mom, Jade...

53
00:03:21,100 --> 00:03:22,533
she'll take care of you.

54
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:24,267
Right, Mookie?

55
00:03:24,400 --> 00:03:25,633
Yes.

56
00:03:32,033 --> 00:03:36,833
Ligaya, are your friends' houses
already near?

57
00:03:36,967 --> 00:03:38,233
Kutsy and Wiro, right?

58
00:03:38,367 --> 00:03:39,500
Yes.

59
00:03:39,633 --> 00:03:45,000
I thought of going to the
police, but I couldn't do it.

60
00:03:45,133 --> 00:03:49,067
No matter what Olive did to me,

61
00:03:49,200 --> 00:03:52,533
I don't think I can bear
to see her suffer

62
00:03:52,667 --> 00:03:53,867
and see her life getting ruined.

63
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,367
Ligaya.

64
00:03:55,533 --> 00:03:57,600
- Ligaya.
- What?

65
00:03:57,733 --> 00:03:59,367
I feel nervous.

66
00:03:59,500 --> 00:04:00,267
Why?

67
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:04,467
Wiro and Kutsy might call
the police

68
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:08,133
if we tell them about Olive.

69
00:04:08,267 --> 00:04:10,200
My friends are not like that.

70
00:04:10,333 --> 00:04:11,667
They'll listen to me.

71
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:17,567
And they'll help me find
a doctor that can help Olive.

72
00:04:17,700 --> 00:04:22,167
They'll understand me if I want
Olive to get treated first.

73
00:04:22,300 --> 00:04:26,733
She'll pay for everything
she did to me once she's better.

74
00:04:26,867 --> 00:04:27,600
Let's go.

75
00:04:29,767 --> 00:04:31,700
I've finally found you,
Miss Ligaya.

76
00:04:50,533 --> 00:04:51,300
Miss Ligaya.

77
00:04:55,033 --> 00:04:55,933
Darn you!

78
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:03,967
Ligaya?

79
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:06,933
Ligaya.

80
00:05:09,833 --> 00:05:11,067
Ligaya.

81
00:05:18,867 --> 00:05:20,200
Ligaya!

82
00:05:20,333 --> 00:05:21,533
You demon!

83
00:05:25,300 --> 00:05:26,933
Come back here!

84
00:05:42,033 --> 00:05:43,000
Hello, Ma'am Jade.

85
00:05:44,333 --> 00:05:45,700
I've already found Miss Ligaya.

86
00:05:51,267 --> 00:05:52,333
Ligaya!

87
00:06:10,333 --> 00:06:11,767
Rise and shine!

88
00:06:14,233 --> 00:06:15,200
My daughter?

89
00:06:15,333 --> 00:06:17,500
Yes, it's me.

90
00:06:17,633 --> 00:06:19,500
Welcome back to your hell.

91
00:06:20,633 --> 00:06:22,533
Hey you.

92
00:06:22,667 --> 00:06:25,333
You almost got me in trouble.

93
00:06:25,467 --> 00:06:30,100
But luckily, I was able
to bring you back here.

94
00:06:30,233 --> 00:06:37,533
And you will never get out
of here until your last breath.

95
00:06:41,567 --> 00:06:42,433
Where's Ador?

96
00:06:43,533 --> 00:06:45,367
What did you do to Ador?

97
00:06:45,500 --> 00:06:46,467
Who's that?

98
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:48,267
She was with a man earlier.

99
00:06:50,167 --> 00:06:51,033
Where is he?

100
00:06:51,167 --> 00:06:53,000
I shot him and left him
on the street.

101
00:06:53,133 --> 00:06:54,000
What?

102
00:06:55,833 --> 00:06:58,833
You can't do that.
Dear, go back to him.

103
00:06:58,967 --> 00:07:01,867
Go see him.
Bring him to the hospital!

104
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:02,867
And why?

105
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:09,267
Why would we waste our time
doing that?

106
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:10,633
He's your father.

107
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:18,133
To be fair with you, Ligaya.

108
00:07:18,267 --> 00:07:21,267
You never fail to amuse me.

109
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:27,300
How did you get a love life
in such a short time?

110
00:07:27,433 --> 00:07:31,733
And he's my father?

111
00:07:31,867 --> 00:07:33,800
You really are something.

112
00:07:35,233 --> 00:07:37,300
Dear, believe me.

113
00:07:37,433 --> 00:07:38,900
I'm telling the truth.

114
00:07:39,033 --> 00:07:41,733
He told me about his
mental condition.

115
00:07:43,033 --> 00:07:46,033
You both have the same symptoms.

116
00:07:46,167 --> 00:07:47,667
You got that...

117
00:07:47,833 --> 00:07:49,600
Got what?

118
00:07:49,733 --> 00:07:50,633
What is it?

119
00:07:52,033 --> 00:07:54,467
What you're going through, dear.

120
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:56,867
I'm not crazy!

121
00:07:59,533 --> 00:08:01,067
Look at you.

122
00:08:01,200 --> 00:08:04,633
First, you abandoned me.

123
00:08:04,767 --> 00:08:07,167
And then you lied.

124
00:08:07,300 --> 00:08:13,100
And now, you're making up
stupid stories and telling me

125
00:08:13,233 --> 00:08:15,067
that I have a mental problem?

126
00:08:16,967 --> 00:08:18,567
You and Emma are the same.

127
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:21,967
Leave Emma out of this.

128
00:08:22,133 --> 00:08:23,200
That girl...

129
00:08:25,100 --> 00:08:27,267
never fails to amaze me, too...

130
00:08:27,400 --> 00:08:28,567
just like you.

131
00:08:29,700 --> 00:08:34,533
She pretended to be dead
to haunt me.

132
00:08:34,667 --> 00:08:37,000
To drive me crazy.

133
00:08:37,133 --> 00:08:38,833
Emma's alive?

134
00:08:38,967 --> 00:08:42,767
Unfortunately,
she's still alive.

135
00:08:44,067 --> 00:08:45,967
But don't celebrate yet.

136
00:08:47,433 --> 00:08:50,933
Because I'm still out to get
your favorite daughter.

137
00:08:52,933 --> 00:08:53,900
Dear, please stop.

138
00:08:54,033 --> 00:08:55,200
I'm begging you.

139
00:08:55,367 --> 00:08:56,667
Please stop.

140
00:08:56,800 --> 00:08:59,100
Remove the hatred in your heart,
dear.

141
00:09:00,267 --> 00:09:02,067
You two are the only ones left.

142
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:03,833
She's your sister.

143
00:09:03,967 --> 00:09:05,867
Shut up!

144
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:06,833
Caloy!

145
00:09:10,767 --> 00:09:12,567
You can now leave, Caloy.

146
00:09:12,700 --> 00:09:16,467
Use the backdoor.
And don't make any noise.

147
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:17,533
Yes, Ma'am.

148
00:09:19,667 --> 00:09:21,667
And as for you, Ligaya,

149
00:09:23,433 --> 00:09:28,633
thank you for finding
your way back into me.

150
00:09:28,800 --> 00:09:32,767
I've finished another task
on my to-do list.

151
00:09:32,900 --> 00:09:39,033
So now, I want you to regain
your strength.

152
00:09:39,167 --> 00:09:41,700
Gather all your energy.

153
00:09:41,833 --> 00:09:44,067
Because you'll need it to
endure everything

154
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:46,467
I will do to you.

155
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:56,567
You'll feel every tear,
every scream, and every pain.

156
00:10:05,933 --> 00:10:07,100
Rest well.

157
00:10:44,667 --> 00:10:47,667
<i>I received an inquiry
from Artemis.</i>

158
00:10:47,800 --> 00:10:51,200
<i>That's Olive's company,
which Jade runs now.</i>

159
00:10:53,067 --> 00:10:55,433
<i>They want to book the bar
for an event.</i>

160
00:10:56,500 --> 00:10:58,200
<i> I want to accept it.</i>

161
00:10:58,333 --> 00:11:02,533
<i>Because I think this is
the right time for our face-off.</i>

162
00:11:02,667 --> 00:11:05,833
<i>This is the right time to
take Mookie back from her.</i>

163
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:08,133
Emma.

164
00:11:09,600 --> 00:11:13,033
I added more men for the
Artemis event.

165
00:11:14,400 --> 00:11:17,000
So that if Jade made a scene,

166
00:11:17,133 --> 00:11:18,300
it'll be easier for you
to escape.

167
00:11:18,433 --> 00:11:19,833
I won't back down.

168
00:11:19,967 --> 00:11:25,400
No soldier is charging into
battle armed only with courage.

169
00:11:26,567 --> 00:11:32,767
Sometimes, even the best
fighters back down.

170
00:11:32,900 --> 00:11:37,367
Not because they are coward
but because they are smart.

171
00:11:38,567 --> 00:11:39,800
They think.

172
00:11:41,500 --> 00:11:43,300
You're ready to fight.

173
00:11:43,433 --> 00:11:44,800
I see that.

174
00:11:45,900 --> 00:11:51,600
But don't forget that your
enemy is also prepared.

175
00:11:54,733 --> 00:12:02,533
And sometimes, crazy people are
more excited to win.

176
00:12:04,567 --> 00:12:09,100
Remember, both camps are
fighting for something.

177
00:12:09,233 --> 00:12:12,433
In your case, it's Mookie.

178
00:12:12,567 --> 00:12:14,600
You both want to win.

179
00:12:14,767 --> 00:12:16,633
So don't be complacent.

180
00:12:16,767 --> 00:12:20,267
I will only relax once
I have Mookie back.

181
00:12:29,033 --> 00:12:30,167
Okay, Astrid.

182
00:12:30,300 --> 00:12:32,633
Let's finalize the details
when I get there.

183
00:12:32,767 --> 00:12:33,800
Bye.

184
00:12:36,100 --> 00:12:37,467
Jade.

185
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:39,700
Leticia, why are you here?

186
00:12:39,833 --> 00:12:42,667
Didn't we agree to meet
with Astrid at the office?

187
00:12:42,800 --> 00:12:46,133
A riding-in-tandem shot
my partner.

188
00:12:46,267 --> 00:12:48,300
He's in the hospital right now.
His condition is critical.

189
00:12:48,467 --> 00:12:51,200
What are you doing here?
Go there!

190
00:12:51,333 --> 00:12:53,400
I need money for his operation.

191
00:12:53,533 --> 00:12:55,467
I can't access his bank account.

192
00:12:55,600 --> 00:12:56,367
What's wrong with you?

193
00:12:56,500 --> 00:12:57,967
You shouldn't have come.

194
00:12:58,100 --> 00:12:59,667
You should've just called me.

195
00:12:59,800 --> 00:13:01,067
How much do you need?

196
00:13:05,767 --> 00:13:06,533
Here.

197
00:13:06,667 --> 00:13:09,367
That's as good as cash.
Go on. Go.

198
00:13:09,500 --> 00:13:11,600
Take care of your business.
I'm gonna be fine.

199
00:13:11,733 --> 00:13:12,633
What about you?

200
00:13:13,700 --> 00:13:15,067
I'll be fine.

201
00:13:15,200 --> 00:13:16,800
Everything's okay.

202
00:13:16,933 --> 00:13:18,633
My meds are working well.

203
00:13:18,767 --> 00:13:20,633
Ligaya is back.

204
00:13:20,767 --> 00:13:24,600
And Astrid is also back
to take care of Artemis.

205
00:13:24,767 --> 00:13:26,833
Now, I can focus more on Emma,

206
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:33,833
especially after the Artemis'
20th anniversary.

207
00:13:33,967 --> 00:13:35,033
But you need me there.

208
00:13:35,167 --> 00:13:36,000
Go!

209
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:55,733
You're so beautiful.

210
00:13:58,300 --> 00:13:59,867
Your smile is the only thing
missing.

211
00:14:01,333 --> 00:14:03,567
I'm nervous, Logan.

212
00:14:03,700 --> 00:14:06,700
What if I can't tell her
everything I want to say?

213
00:14:06,833 --> 00:14:09,967
What if I can't control myself,
and I hurt Jade?

214
00:14:10,100 --> 00:14:11,100
What if...

215
00:14:15,700 --> 00:14:17,133
Relax.

216
00:14:18,300 --> 00:14:20,600
You only need to intimidate
them.

217
00:14:22,033 --> 00:14:23,900
Show them you are so much alive.

218
00:14:25,967 --> 00:14:28,100
And you will never let them win
again.

219
00:14:29,333 --> 00:14:29,967
And...

220
00:14:34,267 --> 00:14:39,400
you're so ready to take your
daughter back.

221
00:14:51,567 --> 00:14:53,433
So everything's ready
for tonight?

222
00:14:53,567 --> 00:14:55,767
Yes, the venue is perfect.

223
00:14:55,900 --> 00:14:56,933
It's so beautiful.

224
00:14:57,067 --> 00:14:59,133
And the food is amazing.

225
00:14:59,267 --> 00:14:59,833
Good.

226
00:15:01,467 --> 00:15:03,267
All the guests have confirmed.

227
00:15:03,400 --> 00:15:04,167
Good!

228
00:15:04,300 --> 00:15:05,633
Yes.
And everyone's gonna be there.

229
00:15:05,767 --> 00:15:07,967
And I'm excited for the
food to be served

230
00:15:08,100 --> 00:15:10,167
because their food is so good.

231
00:15:10,300 --> 00:15:11,933
The drinks are all ready.

232
00:15:12,067 --> 00:15:13,767
Everything you requested is
there.

233
00:15:13,900 --> 00:15:17,933
So, I think everybody will
ave a really, really good time.

234
00:15:35,700 --> 00:15:36,700
Why?

235
00:15:37,900 --> 00:15:39,500
I saw Emma.

236
00:15:39,633 --> 00:15:41,600
She was with us in the elevator.

237
00:15:43,300 --> 00:15:43,800
Emma?

238
00:15:43,967 --> 00:15:44,800
She's here?

239
00:15:44,933 --> 00:15:46,300
Yes, she's here!

240
00:15:46,433 --> 00:15:47,400
I saw her!

241
00:15:49,400 --> 00:15:52,933
Maybe you think about her too
much.

242
00:15:53,067 --> 00:15:55,133
That's why you see her
everywhere.

243
00:15:55,267 --> 00:15:57,200
Let's go inside.

244
00:15:58,367 --> 00:15:59,433
Come on.

245
00:16:12,333 --> 00:16:13,333
Hello.

246
00:16:13,700 --> 00:16:15,267
Please get my clothes
in the car.

247
00:16:19,600 --> 00:16:21,967
20 years.

248
00:16:22,100 --> 00:16:28,200
20 years of excellence,
dedication, and hard work.

249
00:16:28,333 --> 00:16:31,400
Those are just some
of what Artemis

250
00:16:31,533 --> 00:16:33,833
has proven throughout the
years.

251
00:16:33,967 --> 00:16:37,400
And I have each of you to thank

252
00:16:37,533 --> 00:16:41,600
because you're the ones who make
up this company.

253
00:16:41,767 --> 00:16:42,633
Yes?

254
00:16:46,633 --> 00:16:48,800
I know that Artemis Pharmacy

255
00:16:48,933 --> 00:16:51,933
is the baby of my big sister,
Olive.

256
00:16:55,233 --> 00:16:56,700
Now that she's gone,

257
00:16:58,433 --> 00:17:00,967
I want to reassure all of you

258
00:17:01,100 --> 00:17:07,433
that I will continue the good
practices she had started.

259
00:17:08,600 --> 00:17:12,500
So, here's to a better...

260
00:17:12,633 --> 00:17:14,933
brighter Artemis.

261
00:17:27,700 --> 00:17:29,467
Good evening, everyone.

262
00:17:31,067 --> 00:17:35,167
For those who don't know me,
I'm Emma Joseco.

263
00:17:37,300 --> 00:17:39,633
And I'm one of the people
who will prove

264
00:17:39,767 --> 00:17:44,467
that our beloved company's
medicines are so effective.

265
00:17:45,667 --> 00:17:46,967
Do you know why?

266
00:17:49,433 --> 00:17:52,700
Because their medicines
can change a person.

267
00:17:54,233 --> 00:17:57,067
And your minds can be easily...

268
00:17:57,200 --> 00:17:58,367
Cheers!

269
00:17:58,500 --> 00:18:00,200
Cheers, everyone!

270
00:18:00,333 --> 00:18:02,733
Cheers!

271
00:18:02,867 --> 00:18:05,333
20 years!

272
00:18:05,467 --> 00:18:08,167
Congratulations to us!

273
00:18:08,300 --> 00:18:10,767
Cheers!

274
00:18:10,900 --> 00:18:12,933
Cheers!

275
00:18:13,067 --> 00:18:14,733
Enjoy the party!

276
00:18:20,800 --> 00:18:22,833
What are you doing in my event?

277
00:18:25,533 --> 00:18:27,300
I knew it.

278
00:18:27,433 --> 00:18:30,200
Your conscience is still dark

279
00:18:30,333 --> 00:18:32,433
even if you're wearing
pure white.

280
00:18:33,500 --> 00:18:35,533
And despite pretending
to be nice at first,

281
00:18:36,833 --> 00:18:39,867
you're no different
from your twin sister.

282
00:18:43,600 --> 00:18:45,100
So I was right.

283
00:18:45,233 --> 00:18:47,167
It was you that I saw.

284
00:18:51,100 --> 00:18:51,767
<i> Emma?</i>

285
00:18:53,100 --> 00:18:53,700
<i> Emma!</i>

286
00:18:58,200 --> 00:19:00,433
I didn't want to believe
at first.

287
00:19:01,767 --> 00:19:04,233
I was so worried about you,
Emma.

288
00:19:04,367 --> 00:19:06,400
I thought something bad happened
to you.

289
00:19:06,533 --> 00:19:07,600
But...

290
00:19:09,400 --> 00:19:13,167
you seem to be doing well.

291
00:19:13,300 --> 00:19:17,867
In fact,
you look very different.

292
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:21,700
Very different
from the Emma I know.

293
00:19:23,633 --> 00:19:27,833
I had to change myself
to recover

294
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:30,433
from everything you did to me.

295
00:19:30,567 --> 00:19:31,733
Me?

296
00:19:34,400 --> 00:19:36,367
What are you talking about?

297
00:19:36,500 --> 00:19:38,767
What wrong did I do to you?

298
00:19:38,900 --> 00:19:41,800
Emma, I was so worried about
you.

299
00:19:41,933 --> 00:19:44,167
I thought you were already dead.

300
00:19:44,300 --> 00:19:47,633
I almost put your picture
on an altar at home.

301
00:19:47,767 --> 00:19:48,667
You know...

302
00:19:48,800 --> 00:19:52,067
just in case you struggle
to go to heaven.

303
00:19:54,267 --> 00:19:56,000
I'm so much alive.

304
00:19:56,133 --> 00:19:57,900
What do you think of me?

305
00:19:58,033 --> 00:19:59,200
A ghost?

306
00:20:01,500 --> 00:20:07,367
What do you call a person
who disappears like a bubble?

307
00:20:07,533 --> 00:20:08,733
Isn't it a ghost?

308
00:20:10,933 --> 00:20:16,000
I escaped from the mental
facility because I wasn't crazy.

309
00:20:16,133 --> 00:20:20,767
And I know you caused all
my sufferings in that place.

310
00:20:22,167 --> 00:20:23,967
Oh dear, Emma.

311
00:20:27,333 --> 00:20:30,167
I really don't know what
you're talking about.

312
00:20:30,300 --> 00:20:37,500
Because the truth is you left
and pushed your family away.

313
00:20:37,667 --> 00:20:43,467
You left to stay away from them.

314
00:20:44,833 --> 00:20:49,433
Because you would've come back
if you loved them.

315
00:20:50,500 --> 00:20:52,500
You would show yourself to them.

316
00:20:54,900 --> 00:21:00,333
But you didn't.

317
00:21:01,500 --> 00:21:07,233
I did everything to see
and be with my family.

318
00:21:07,367 --> 00:21:09,600
But what will I come home to?

319
00:21:09,767 --> 00:21:11,967
You and Danilo getting married?

320
00:21:12,100 --> 00:21:15,033
Mookie has been acknowledging
you as her mother?

321
00:21:15,167 --> 00:21:17,867
That my family is happy
with you?

322
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:20,400
They forgot about me
just like that.

323
00:21:22,400 --> 00:21:25,667
Those wouldn't happen

324
00:21:25,800 --> 00:21:30,467
if you weren't a negligent
mother and wife.

325
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:32,733
You ruined my life!

326
00:21:32,867 --> 00:21:35,567
You planned everything
to steal them from me.

327
00:21:37,133 --> 00:21:38,933
You ruined my life!

328
00:21:39,567 --> 00:21:42,267
You planned everything
to steal them from me.

329
00:21:42,433 --> 00:21:43,733
Oh, please, Emma.

330
00:21:44,733 --> 00:21:49,067
Stop blaming me for things
that you did to yourself.

331
00:21:49,200 --> 00:21:56,400
You're the one who ruined your
life and family.

332
00:21:57,533 --> 00:21:58,433
And another thing.

333
00:21:59,400 --> 00:22:01,467
What are you doing in my party?

334
00:22:03,267 --> 00:22:04,467
Guard!

335
00:22:05,467 --> 00:22:08,567
Take this crazy gatecrasher
out of here.

336
00:22:14,233 --> 00:22:15,567
What?

337
00:22:15,733 --> 00:22:18,000
Why aren't you doing anything?

338
00:22:18,133 --> 00:22:21,267
Do you want me to call
the manager of this bar?

339
00:22:23,967 --> 00:22:25,333
What?

340
00:22:25,467 --> 00:22:27,233
She's in front of you.

341
00:22:31,400 --> 00:22:32,833
Excuse me?

342
00:22:32,967 --> 00:22:35,067
You heard me, didn't you?

343
00:22:36,367 --> 00:22:38,233
I'm the manager of this bar.

344
00:22:38,367 --> 00:22:41,867
So talk to me if you need
anything.

345
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:49,467
Love, look!

346
00:22:49,633 --> 00:22:51,533
Astrid sent it to me.

347
00:22:51,667 --> 00:22:53,533
She looks like she became
wealthy.

348
00:22:53,667 --> 00:22:57,567
Isn't it because of
the man she's hugging?

349
00:22:57,700 --> 00:23:01,467
I wonder why we couldn't
see Emma

350
00:23:01,600 --> 00:23:03,267
when we were looking for her.

351
00:23:03,400 --> 00:23:05,433
This isn't true!

352
00:23:05,567 --> 00:23:07,967
The nerve of you to come here.

353
00:23:08,100 --> 00:23:10,633
The other day, you stole
the scene in my event,

354
00:23:10,767 --> 00:23:13,000
and now you're hovering around
Mookie at school.

355
00:23:13,133 --> 00:23:14,500
I have the right to come here.

356
00:23:14,633 --> 00:23:18,167
I can make Mookie
choose between us.

357
00:23:18,300 --> 00:23:21,400
And it's no doubt that
she'll choose me.

358
00:23:21,533 --> 00:23:23,767
I'm planning to confess
my feelings to Emma.

359
00:23:23,933 --> 00:23:27,033
Emma's so busy
with her daughter.

360
00:23:27,167 --> 00:23:29,333
Does she still have time
to be in a relationship?

361
00:23:29,467 --> 00:23:32,767
She won't say no because
she's indebted to me.

362
00:23:32,900 --> 00:23:34,967
I took care of her.

363
00:23:35,100 --> 00:23:38,067
I took her in and invested
a lot in her.

364
00:23:38,200 --> 00:23:41,200
She'll be ashamed to reject me.

365
00:23:43,667 --> 00:23:44,500
Dan?
